Next, we use a nested loop to iterate over all possible pairs of cities (i and j), and if i and j share a common divisor greater than the threshold, we connect them in the data structure. Note that we start the inner loop at 2 * i since we don't need to consider divisors less than i. After finding and connecting all cities that share a common divisor and satisfy the condition, we can then iterate through the queries and check if the cities in the query are connected using the find function. If they are connected, we return true, otherwise false for the corresponding query.

